## Kit Setup (for agents)

To set up agentic-kit in a project, run from the **project root** (the directory that contains `.agentic-kit/`):

```bash
.agentic-kit/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=claude    # Claude Code: .claude/, CLAUDE.md
.agentic-kit/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=cursor   # Cursor: .cursor/skills/, .cursor/rules/*.mdc, AGENTS.md
.agentic-kit/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=github  # Copilot: .github/agents/, .github/instructions/
.agentic-kit/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=all      # all three (alias: --ide=both)
```

Non-interactive flags: `-n`, `--non-interactive`, `--yes`, or `-y`. The script prints a **`[AGENT ACTION REQUIRED]`** block instead of spawning a nested CLI to edit `PROJECT.md`.

**After the script exits, fill in `PROJECT.md` yourself:** inspect the project files (`package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, `Cargo.toml`, `go.mod`, `Makefile`, version files, etc.) and replace every `<placeholder>` with the correct value. Then run `.agentic-kit/tools/validate-config.sh` to confirm all placeholders are resolved.

**What each `--ide` produces (high level):**

| Target | Skills | Agents / rules | Pipeline doc |
|--------|--------|----------------|----------------|
| `claude` | Symlinks → `.claude/skills/` | Symlinks → `.claude/agents/` | `CLAUDE.md` (copy of this template) |
| `cursor` | Symlinks → `.cursor/skills/` (and `.claude/skills/` for bundled shell scripts) | Generated `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (agents + `pipeline.mdc`) | `AGENTS.md` |
| `github` | `.github/instructions/*.instructions.md` | `.github/agents/*.agent.md` | `.github/copilot-instructions.md` |
| `all` | All of the above | All of the above | All of the above |

